{{Glossary
|Entry=Lexical Unit
|Description=Lexical units that are associated with a given frame are listed in the 'Relevant Lexical Units' section of the Frame entry. 

Each lexical unit is listed in its lemma form, followed by a part of speech tag, with the two elements separated by a period.  

The part of speech tags currently in use are:
  noun = n
  verb = v
  adjective = a
  adverb = adv  

Example entries for the Election frame:
   election.n
   elect.v
|Applies to=Frame
